<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19112] Unifying LIST-Type Configuration Validation and Default Values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19112</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, we allow a user to set&#160;cleanup.policy to be an empty list, which shouldn&apos;t be allowed. A few other configs of List type such as&lt;br/&gt;
group.coordinator.rebalance.protocols and process.roles have the same problem.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13614618">KAFKA-19112</key>
            <summary>Unifying LIST-Type Configuration Validation and Default Values</summary>
