                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17942029" author="junrao" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2025 23:46:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can tighten up the validation for those configs. However, not sure about incorrect values already in place. One option is to just fail fast in that case. We probably need a KIP if we do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17942030" author="JIRAUSER305187" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2025 23:51:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=junrao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;junrao&quot;&gt;junrao&lt;/a&gt;&#160; if you won&#8217;t work on this, may I take it, Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17942034" author="junrao" created="Wed, 9 Apr 2025 00:11:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=m1a2st&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;m1a2st&quot;&gt;m1a2st&lt;/a&gt; : Thanks for your interest. Feel free to take it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17943826" author="chia7712" created="Sat, 12 Apr 2025 14:55:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=junrao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;junrao&quot;&gt;junrao&lt;/a&gt; Leaving empty means users don&apos;t want to either delete or compact segment files. It makes sense to me if users want to keep those data forever.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944402" author="junrao" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2025 16:11:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chia7712&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chia7712&quot;&gt;chia7712&lt;/a&gt; : For infinite retention, we already support that through the following config. Relying on empty cleanup.policy seems redundant and unintuitive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;https%3A%2F%2Fkafka.apache.org%2Fdocumentation%2F%23broker...&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/#brokerconfigs_log.retention.ms&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/#brokerconfigs_log.retention.ms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
log.retention.ms
The number of milliseconds to keep a log file before deleting it (in milliseconds), If not set, the value in log.retention.minutes is used. If set to -1, no time limit is applied.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944413" author="chia7712" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2025 17:00:51 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Replying on empty cleanup.policy seems redundant and unintuitive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Users need to set both retention.ms and retention.bytes to -1 to ensure the infinite retention, and I preferred to use one button to address it. However, I agree the &quot;empty&quot; list is unintuitive, so +1 to disallow the empty config.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944435" author="ijuma" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2025 18:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could also allow the cleanup.policy to have the value `none` - it does seem like a more direct way of saying you don&apos;t want to delete/compact.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944438" author="chia7712" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2025 18:34:48 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We could also allow the cleanup.policy to have the value `none`&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sounds good to me. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=m1a2st&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;m1a2st&quot;&gt;m1a2st&lt;/a&gt; Could you please consider adding it to KIP?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944536" author="JIRAUSER305187" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2025 00:26:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I will add it to KIP&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
